competitors.name: Shia Masjid and Imam Hussain as. Imambada

places.address: V238+P57 Masjid - E - Hadid, Marwari Para, Jharsuguda, Odisha 768201

featured_reviews.review_id: It's believed that Masjid - e - Hadid of Jharsuguda is only 2nd in entire Asia, which is built of Iron frame. That's why, it is called Masjid - e - Hadid or Mosque of Iron. It was built by a Gujarati person, who was resident of Sambalpur ( Odisha ). The beauty of this mosque lies in the Dome, a minaret and ceiling of Prayer hall. The entire structure is unique in it's Concept and Design. Though, a small in size, in comparison to other mosques, which we see around, it's one of it's kind. If you believe the people associated with this place, the entire structure ( mosque ) can be moved to other place, if required. Now, concrete wall has been built around the main structure, you can still see and feel the uniqueness of this mosque from inside. Seeing is believing...
